      "body": "Considering:\r\n```\r\n$ ls -l\r\nwallet_sym.dat -> wallet.dat\r\n```\r\nThe following tests fail:\r\n\r\nTest 1 :\r\n```\r\nbitcoind -regtest -wallet=wallet_sym.dat\r\nError: Invalid -wallet path ... -wallet path should point to ...\r\n```\r\nTest 2:\r\n```\r\nbitcoind -regtest -wallet=w1\r\nbitcoin-cli -regtest loadwallet wallet_sym.dat\r\nerror code: -4\r\nerror message:\r\nWallet file verification failed: Invalid -wallet path 'wallet_sym.dat'. -wallet path should point to ...\r\n```\r\nCould you share your test?\r\n\r\nNote that it is possible to have links if it's a directory (`where wallet.dat and database/log.?????????? files can be stored`).",
